    {
      "id": "868298053044333",
      "score": 4,
      "review_title": "Pretty good game!",
      "review_description": "So far I have played and beaten chapter 1 of the horror mode and have explored the shop and some of the spawn area, this game from my expierence is pretty good! The concept is great, I really enjoyed the levels, and the monster designs and cosmetics are great! The level designs are also amazing and just love them\n\nNow there are some things about this game I did not like. For starters it can be laggy at times, like I would get stuck to the ground and would be hard to move. It could either just be my headset or the fact I have URP on. Also when I tried recording with the LIV camera it made my game super laggy in a public! Even with URP off it was still very bad. Another thing is the game for me broke a little bit at time, so it would sometimes spawn me out of the map, when dying in the spikes part of chapter 1 it kept me spawned in the air and I couldn't get down for some reason. Another thing is escpecially when trying to move onto chapter 2 for some reason when going into the teleporter I would just spawn in the chapter 1 ending and fall right into the lava a whole bunch, making it very annoying when trying to continue. Also chapter 1 could be more scarier becuase for me it wasn't scary at all and the monsters were easily jukable. \n\n\nOther than that the game is very good and I would HIGHLY reccomended for a good time!",
      "date": 1767402820,
      "review_helpful_count": 3,
      "author_display_name": "BowSpecs",
      "author_alias": "BowSpecs",
      "developer_response": null
    },
